&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post Anaesthetic Care Unit Advert: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PACU ADVERT &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have 2 wte vacancies for Registered Nurses or ODP’s at Band 5 in our Post Anaesthetic Care Unit (Recovery) at the Royal Stoke University Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will gain a wide range of experience and can expand your skills and knowledge in this challenging environment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for dynamic, enthusiastic candidates with the ability to work well within a busy dynamic unit, and who can deliver high quality patient care.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In turn, we can offer you a structured preceptorship and induction programme for all new members of staff, plus access to on-going continuing professional education and development, appraisal and clinical supervision.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;All staff are welcome to apply, ideally we are looking for experienced team members but we welcome applications from newly qualified staff / or new to PACU who can demonstrate a keen interest in joining our team and the desire to offer high quality patient care. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff need to be able to work flexibly to cover the full service requirements over the 24 hour period which includes a full range of rotational shifts Early, Lates and Nights , Weekends and occasional on-calls.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Important Information:&lt;br /&gt;Please note the University Hospitals of North Midlands (NHS) Trust, do not pay travel expenses for candidates attending interviews&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coordinator Sheila Cooper Sheila.Cooper@uhnm.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister Angela Johnson AngelaJ.Johnson@uhnm.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister Michelle Fell Michelle.Fell@uhns.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or in their absence :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matron Julie Turner JulieA.Turner@uhnm.nhs.uk ,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matron Andrew Cole andrew.col@uhnm.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
